snippet.textDisplay: I miss my Dad. When he turned 40,  he bought a new truck ( his first new vehicle ever) a 1972 (Chevy 3/4 ton, 292 six with 4 speed manual.  RADIO DELETE., no carpet, base interior,. So, in 1974, I saved up my money and bought him a AM FM Cassette deck for his birthday. I installed it and surprised him with it.  During the reveal  my Dad looked me in my face and said. “ If I had wanted a radio in my truck, I would have bought one.”   The next day I found the entire system on the porch by my front door.  My Dad was a mean, tough S.O.B.
